'''Bruce Robert Gregory''' (May 13, 1903 &ndash; December 1960) was an [[American football]] player.  A native of [[Battle Creek, Michigan]], Gregory played [[Halfback (American football)|halfback]] for the [[Michigan Wolverines football]] team from 1924 to 1925.<ref>{{cite web|title=1925 Football Team|publisher=University of Michigan, Bentley Historical Library|url=http://bentley.umich.edu/athdept/football/fbteam/1925fbt.htm}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=1924 Football Team|publisher=University of Michigan, Bentley Historical Library|url=http://bentley.umich.edu/athdept/football/fbteam/1924fbt.htm}}</ref>  Gregory later played professional football for the [[Detroit Panthers]] in 1926.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bruce Gregory profile|publisher=pro-football-reference.com|url=http://www.pro-football-reference.com/players/G/GregBr20.htm}}</ref>  He played in all 12 games for the Panthers in 1926, including 11 games as a starter. Gregory later became a tire dealer.<ref>{{cite news|author=Jerry Ledonne|title=MICHIGAN DENIES AWARD GIVEN TO FOOTBALL STAR|newspaper=Chicago Daily Tribune|date=1951-08-09|page=B3}}</ref>

